  <properties>
    <property name="family">Power Supply Charger</property>
    <property name="variant">eFlow102NB</property>
    <property name="part number">eFlow102NB</property>
    <property name="dimensions">Red Max 1:1 calibrated 5.4273 in x 3.1752 in</property>
    <property name="output">12VDC 10A</property>
    <property name="input">120VAC 60Hz 3.5A</property>
    <property name="mounting pattern">Upper Red Max power-supply slot</property>
    <property name="mounting hole spacing">4.7238 in x 2.5802 in</property>
    <property name="calibration source">Red Max exact 1368 x 1752 px image at 96 DPI</property>
    <property name="SVG coordinate density">72 units per inch</property>
    <property name="renderer compatibility">Plain default SVG namespace; no generated ns0 prefixes</property>
  </properties>
  <description>Altronix eFlow102NB UL Listed sub-assembly power supply/charger. Converts 120VAC 60Hz input to a regulated 12VDC output rated 10A continuous. Includes standby battery charging, AC and battery failure Form-C supervision, supervised fire alarm disconnect interface, and an unswitched 1A auxiliary output. Breadboard dimensions use the official approximate board dimensions of 7.5 x 4.6 inches. This custom Fritzing part is intended for enclosure layout and wiring documentation. Recalibrated against the exact 1368 x 1752 px, 96 DPI Red Max enclosure artwork. Target pattern: Upper Red Max power-supply slot; mounting-hole spacing 4.7238 x 2.5802 inches. Resulting breadboard footprint: 5.4273 x 3.1752 inches. This revision removes generated namespace prefixes that can break Qt/Fritzing SVG rendering and normalizes every SVG view to 72 coordinate units per physical inch, matching established Fritzing part conventions.</description>
